Martin B. Anstice 

		
		President and CEO, 

	
		 Lam Research Corporation 	

 
Last Updated: 02/07/2017 



Executive Summary
Martin Anstice started his career at Raychem Corporation in 1988.  He spent thirteen years at the technology company, which was recognized as one of the fastest growing companies in the U.S. at the time.  At Raychem, Anstice held numerous finance and business management roles, both domes 
Current Focus

Company Snapshot: Lam Research is a trusted global supplier of innovative wafer fabrication equipment and services to the semiconductor industry. Lam's broad portfolio of market-leading deposition, etch, and clean s 
Biographical Highlights

Born c. 1968
Anstice began his career at Raychem Corporation in 1988, where he held numerous finance roles in Europe and North America. 
Other Boards and Organizations

Former Member, North America Advisory Board (NAAB), Semiconductor Equipment and Materials International (SEMI)
Associate Member, Chartered Institute of Management Accountants, UK 
Donations and Philanthropy

Mercy High School, Burlingame, CA, 2013

 





